A severe mosaic symptom was noticed in [@Basella rubra L.#Plant*]
during survey of [@cucurbit#Plant*] growing areas for an epidemiological study.
The infected plants were investigated for host range, physical properties, insect transmission and [$ELISA#Method*].
In the preliminary findings, mosaic causing virus appeared to be a strain of [$cucumber mosaic virus#Virus*] ([$CMV#Virus*]) and [@B.rubra#Plant*] as a natural host of [$cucumber mosaic virus#Virus*] ([$CMV#Virus*]).